<p><a href="/scp-4529">SCP-4529: A Walk in the Park</a> (<span style="color: green">+49</span>, <span style="color: firebrick"><sup>&#8230;</sup>17</span>)<br />
<span style="font-size:80%;"><span style="color: grey"><em>Created on <span class="odate time_1582293919 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Feb 2020 14:05</span></em></span></span></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▶&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▷&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My first published SCP. To be honest, I'm immensely proud with how it turned out, especially for my first article, and I was extremely happy when I saw how much it resonated with some people.</p>
<p>The inspiration for this article stemmed from a less-than-favorable trip to an old childhood park of mine. I was mostly expecting to be flooded with nostalgic warmth and happiness while traveling through it, but instead I accidentally uprooted a lot of bad memories (kids being shitty to me, other personal stuff). That was really the impetus for making this &#8212; I wanted to tell a story which related to my own experiences during elementary school and spin it into a weird, shape-shifting anomaly.</p>
<p>The original drafts for this SCP actually included a subplot about a person of interest who made the park to perform a ritual in a nearby hotel to resurrect the memory of their dead friend and &#8212; yeah, I ditched that. In those earlier drafts Poplar was less fleshed-out, and everything was in audio format, so you constantly had characters describing to other characters what happened to Poplar. That got real messy real quick, so I decided to keep it in video format.</p>
<p>One of the last structural changes I made to this was including the interview. Originally, I thought that ending the article at the exploration log would make the ending suspenseful. But then I found that it was way too open-ended of an&#8230; ending to be emotionally satisfying; hence, the interview. I'm actually the most proud of the interview, and I really think it helps give the piece some emotional depth.</p>
<p>My critters were incredibly helpful in bringing fruition to this article, so I'll list their lovely names here:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Idea Critters:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5336470&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="cybersqyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5336470)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;">cybersqyd</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-whitney" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5252186); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5252186&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="Dr Whitney" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5252186)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-whitney" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5252186); return false;">Dr Whitney</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/f15h35" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5938164); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5938164&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="F15H35" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5938164)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/f15h35" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5938164); return false;">F15H35</a></span></p>
<p><strong>Draft Critters:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5336470&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="cybersqyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5336470)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5336470); return false;">cybersqyd</a></span>, DrUnoriginal, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3118444&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="Pedantique" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3118444)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pedantique" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3118444); return false;">Pedantique</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioludoodle" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3165531); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3165531&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721469" alt="rioludoodle" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3165531)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rioludoodle" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3165531); return false;">rioludoodle</a></span></p>
